9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 439, L.D. 671, “An Act to Abolish the
10 Maine Income Tax and Establish a Zero-based Budget”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Abolish the Maine Individual Income Tax and Establish a Zero-based
13 Budget'
14 Amend the bill in Part A in section 1 in c. 843 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 5 in L.D.)
15 by striking out the following: "INCOME TAX ELIMINATION" and inserting the
16 following: 'INDIVIDUAL INCOME TAX ELIMINATION'
17 Amend the bill in Part A in section 1 in c. 843 in §5501 in the first line (page 1, line 6
18 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "of" the following: 'individual'
19 Amend the bill in Part A in section 1 in c. 843 in §5501 in the first indented paragraph
20 in the first line (page 1, line 7 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "no tax may be" and
21 inserting the following: 'individual income tax may not be'
22 Amend the bill in Part A in section 1 in c. 843 by inserting after §5501 the following:
23 '§5502. Individual income tax filing requirements
24 For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, an individual taxpayer with no tax
25 liability that requires the filing of a Maine income tax return is not required to file a return
26 with the State.
27 §5503. Individual income tax credits
28 For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, tax credits may not be collected
29 by individual taxpayers under this Part. Maine income tax credits made available to
30 individual taxpayers under any other Part and collectible under this Part may not be
31 claimed.'
32 Amend the bill in Part B by inserting after section 2 the following:
33 'Sec. B-3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
34 allocations are made.
